# Database ownership

SQLite is owned by the Node API.

The Python AI service must not read from or write to the application database.

# Tables

Keep the schema minimal.

Notes should store:

- id
- original_text
- created_at

Actions should store:

- id
- note_id
- title
- type
- deadline_text
- normalized_deadline
- priority
- evidence
- needs_review
- uncertainty_reason
- review_status
- completion_status
- created_at
- updated_at

# Data integrity

- Every action must reference an existing note.
- Use foreign keys.
- Use allowed values consistently.
- Use timestamps for created_at and updated_at.
- Do not silently overwrite records.
- Update only fields explicitly allowed by the API.
- Preserve original source evidence.

# Simplicity

Do not add an ORM unless explicitly requested.

Prefer a lightweight SQLite library and clearly written repository functions.

Do not add:

- soft deletion
- audit tables
- event sourcing
- database triggers
- caching
- migrations frameworks

unless a concrete project requirement requires them.

# Sensitive data

Use fictional sample data only.

Do not commit real patient information.

Do not log full note content during normal application operation.
